medusa the asynchronous communications framework upon which supervisors server and client code is based was created by sam rushing medusa was once distributed under a free for non commercial use license but in may of 2000 sam rushing changed the license to be identical to the standard python license at the time
the standard python license has always applied to the core components of medusa this change just frees up the rest of the system including the http server ftp server utilities etc

medusa is therefore under the following license permission to use copy modify and distribute this software and its documentation for any purpose and without fee is hereby granted provided that the above copyright notice appear in all copies and that both that copyright notice and this permission notice appear in supporting documentation and that the name of sam rushing not be used in advertising or publicity pertaining to distribution of the software without specific written prior permission
